inn1.comm: strayed down leg, turned round to deep fine leg with a quick tuck off the pads
on the legs once again and tucked round again but this time for a single, but Sreesanth will be encouraged by the swing he is finding
once again that's on the legs, Sreesanth struggling to find his line to the left handers, and Hayden booted that one off the hips with a firm push through backward square
much better line and causes Hayden some trouble there with one which pitches just outside and comes back so close to the forwrad-prodding edge
tucked up on leg, with one which pitches on a good length, Hayden squeezes down and out towards mid-on
swing back in to the left hander, tight line, and pushed out to mid-on without much power
over the wicket, short and wide and Gilchrist hits that very hard indeed, standing back and rocking a strong cut up and over backward point and it goes like lightning across the turf
better line and length, just on off, worked down off the back foot defensively rather than anything
outside off, that swings a long way outside off as the batsman shoulders arms extravagantly
banged wide down the channel, again a big leave
nipped across him with some zig and no little zag, a testing length and the batsman shoulders arms as it goes down the channel
more of the same, and the batsman does well to leave it, too much of a good length
there must be a deliberate plan to bowl wide down the channel because there he goes again, once more left
banged in short and wide and cut hard through point to the ridiculously short boundary
Gilchrist goes again, outside off, and drilled hard on the front foot through cover

what a ripper of a delivery and a good catch - nips it hard back in fro moutside off on a shortish length, Gilchrist jumps into the line and pushes through a nick off an inside edge, Dhoni dives far to his right and takes the ball one-handed
outside off, Ponting bissects the fielders at mid-off and cover with a firm push of a forward defence
shoulders arms there as the ball jags back a touch from outside off, Hayden quick to make sure to evade the ball
defended on the front foot this time, good line and length there
Hayden lifts the ball from outside off with a front-foot straight pull over mid-on
short ball on middle and off, moving away, Hayden simply shoulders the ball all the way over midwicket, and that's rocketed flat
defended on the front foot now
a rearing bouncer outside off, Hayden goes for a big lash of a front foot wallop over mid-on and is nowhere near the ball
pushed up there on off, defended on the front foot
up there on off and defended forward once more
up there on off, defended quietly on the front foot
wide outside off and Ponting cuts hard off the back foot in front of point
just outside off, a good length, Ponting pushes into the covers defensively, Harbhajan shines the ball and returns it in
some room outside off and Ponting leaps on to it with a full-blooded cover drive from the middle of the bat
up there on off, Ponting jumps into the line and defends down on the back foot
width outside off, cut hard in the air over point
oh, nearly! A big dive from Rohit Sharma to his left at point as Ponting shapes to drive forward and takes a huge outside edge
outside off, cut into the covers
another good delivery troubles Ponting once more, the batsman coming outside off but the ball cuts back, he squares up and pops up a leading edge, safe
nipped back in again, Ponting comes forward and defends on the front foot
pushed across him a bit too straight on middle and leg, Ponting clips well off the toes to midwicket
comes out on leg, and defends towards mid-on
drags it too short on off and Hayden disdainfully despatches it with a pull through square leg to bring up Australia's fifty from 37 balls
round the wicket and does well with one that pitches wide outside off and angles a touch back in after pitching
half-volley outside off and Hayden uses all his muscle to boost the ball up and over mid-on and it flies hard and on its way
nipped back in, pushed out to short midwicket
an attempted yorker strays down leg, Ponting turns it off the pads - literally - and the appeal was more in hope than expectation
outside off, good length forces Ponting to adjust his shot and indeed check it into a forward defence
good length pushed across off, the batsman lashes an inside edge hard back towards his sticks and Ishant can't believe Hayden's not dragged that one back on
straight, short and hustled round with a would-be pull, misses, the ball crashes on to his midriff
good length on off, defended back down off the back foot
overpitched on off and Ponting helps himself to a silken on-drive, just a push, and out it travels
outside off, pushed out to the covers
on middle and leg, driven out to mid-on
short on off and that's a majestic shot from Ponting who lifts it off the back foot, swivelling round and smashing over square many rows back
on leg, turned off the toes through gully
fired wide outside off, Hayden goes for the cut shot, crouching into it, but it flies past the base
wide again, cut into the ground outside off and it travels on to Irfan who snatches it
hit across the line into deep midwicket with a forthright drive
a wide again, Hayden coming out to again try to cut but the ball's through him. It's a fair call, the ball in line with marker
outside off, cut down into the covers, hardly firmly struck
strayed onto leg, turned behind square now
nips back in a touch from outside, driven to the covers
pushed across him from over the wicket, Hayden gets into position and sets himself to cut through point
good ball, across him again, this time on a tighter line just outside off and on a good length
outside off and Hayden comes out of his crease to drive up to mid-on, just to say in front of Yuvraj who had plenty of time to take it but instead lets it pop into his knees
outside off, cut down to Sreesanth
outside off, short, and Ponting swivels the ball round from there through in front of midwicket, terrific shot, well balanced and weighted
starts well, quietening the batsman up in front of off, tight length and all Hayden can do is defend back off the back foot
outside off, pushed gently into the short midwicket region
on middle and leg, pushed into short midwicket off the back foot
outside off, pushed to mid-off
good bounce up to the batsman, the ball pitching back in to him and forcing him to defend off the back foot
on leg, turned round through the 45
right up there on a good length on off, pushed down quietly, in defence
right up there on off, a slower ball at 118kph, defended on the front foot
on leg, tight length, but turned down to fine leg
short ball, whipped round from in line with off to midwicket off the back foot
ah, short in front of the fielder at deep third man, Ponting going for the up and over cover, instead it lopoed up and round, bouncing in front of the fielder
outside off, worked into the covers this time
rolls his fingers on it a touch short, Hayden rocks back and forces hard to the covers where Gautam Gambhir does so well with a dive to his right
pushed on to the back foot, defended down
a good yorker, dug out to short midwicket with a dig of a press
plants this one on off now, driven out to mid-on for a gentle single
pushed across him, driven out off the back foot to cover, without much power
on middle, turned away on off, defended back down
outside off, a touch of width, cut hard behind point
driven forward on the front foot back to the bowler
on leg, turend round to square and there was a chance if he had hit from point
shortish on off, pushed out to the covers off the back foot
a hint of swing outside off, pushed into the covers on the front foot
dragged it short outside off, driven out to the covers again
fires in from over the wicket to outside off, cut down into the covers
outside off, and pushed forward into the ground
full delivery on middle, shuffled out to the covers for a quick single
a cramping delivery, full on off and forcing the batsman to come out and press right over the ball to snuff out any threat
down leg, turned round quietly to square
well bowled that time right up there on off, worked off the toes into short midwicket
curve wide outside off, cut hard to gully and taken well by Rohit Sharma with a dive to his right
on off, pushed on to the back foot and defended down
on middle, good line and the length's not bad, but it's driven out square to midwicket
fired in full and flat on middle, defended quietly on the front foot
outside off, pushed out to mid-off for a quick single
outside off, full delivery, Hayden drives hard back towards the bowler and the deflection crashes out to mid-on who picks it up easily
good loop on middle and off, pushed out to mid-off quietly
turns back in from outside leg and is brushed back out to square leg without much fuss
tight ball outside off, looks to try to squeeze it to short midwicket
turned off the legs to midwicket for a quick single
forced well on a good length in line with leg, turned into short midwicket
driven out to mid-off this time
driven out straight to mid-off, the batsmen charge through
a quick drive to mid-on
on off, pushed forward with no alarm
a full toss slips out at hip height and the bowler gets away with it - close to being a no-ball - as the batsman hasn't got enough room to do much with it otehr than push to the covers
driven out to mid-off this time
strayed down leg and Ponting's quick eyes help him react by pulling wristly through square
on off, tucked off the legs square
a glide of a drive out wide of mid-on, Ponting taking that from outside off
on off, pushed to midwicket and they run well indeed
turned square off the legs
good loop outside off, turning away, the batsman comes over and out, and then defends
turns back in from outside off, and turned round out through fine leg where Sreesanth tidies up
well bowled, pushed up on a good length just outside off, the batsman respects the ball wirh a forward defence
waits on off and defends down off the back foot back towards the bowler
tries the cutter at 102.9kph, Ponting waits and turns out to square leg
overpitched on off, and driven hard down the ground for a much-needed confidence boost of a fifty
yorker outside off, pushed out to mid-off
angled down on leg at a full length, Ponting digs out towards short midwicket
defended back to the bowler from outside off
down on one knee to meet a good-length ball and sweep it to midwicket

a bad mix-up there and Hayden's on his way after Ponting drove out to the covers, just wide of the fielder who picks up, turns, sets himself and throws back to Sehwag and Hayden's well out of his crease trying to scramble back
a good-length ball on off is met with a quiet defence
another mix-up to short midwicket and as Clarke runs to get back in his crease they take the single through an overthrow opportunity
turned in from outside off, pushed out towards point with a checked shot
a touch too short and on middle and leg, the batsman gets over the ball and brushes out in front of square
comes out and defends on the front foot
comes down the track to meet the ball outside off, driven out towards mid-on
driven out to mid-on
on middle and leg, turned off the legs in front of square
moves back across his strumps to make room to drive out to mid-on
outside off and cut hard to deep point for a comfortable single
slower ball on off, defended forward given the decent length
Ponting drives in the air, just over short cover, just enough bat on it to get over the man there
on the legs, flicked to backward square
driven out to the covers this time
on the legs, tucked out to short midwicket, and they scramble through the single
outside off, a short ball into the covers, Robin Uthappa gets the direct hit at the non-striker's but it ricochets off to allow them the overthrow
good length on off, driven out to mid-off
outside off, tucks it round to midwicket for a comfortable single
pushed it in a good length and his height helped him get some steepling bounce, the ball jagging in off the seam and defended down well off the back foot
outside off, played down off the back foot to the gully region
overpitches on off, Clarke drives out off the pads and there's some good running for three
the keeper's up by the way, full on off and driven to mid-off
pushed forward again
outside off, driven hard through the covers for a great shot
wide outside off, cut hard off the base of the bat in the air up over to third man where Ishant does well with the slide and they get back for a well-run three
outside off again, cut hard into the ground and it runs down softly to third man now
on leg, turned out to short midwicket and they scramble through
low full toss on leg, driven out to mid-on easily
full toss again, driven out to mid-off
pushed a touch wide down off, the ball straightens and is cut out to point
on off, turned round off the legs behind square
outside off, driven hard to the covers, they race through the single
on off and middle, a slight risk as the batsman paddles the ball in front of the sticks round through the 45
bends it on to leg stump and it's brushed out to square leg
swivelled in on middle and leg, full, and defended on the front foot
outside off, waits on the back foot and drives back out to the covers
checks a drive back to the bowler
outside off, good length, Clarke forces a drive out to mid-off
pushed back to the bowler
up there on leg, driven out to wide mid-on
comes down the track to clip off the legs from in line with off
on off, doesn't quite hold of a drive out to mid-on
an easy drive out to mid-on now
turned off the legs from in line with leg out to midwicket
Clarke backs away and pulls hard through midwicket
outside off, pushed out to short midwicket
backs away and waits on the back foot to carve out to the covers on the toes
steps out to drive to the covers
outside off, width, cut hard through point and the fielder comes round to tidy up
turns in from outside off to middle, cut back out to the covers
driven out to the covers again
veers down leg and it's pulled round to square
flatbatted down the ground with an aerial swat out to long on
waits on the back foot and pushes out to mid-off
defended this time
comes down the track to meet the ball on off and flicks out to midwicket, not quite getting hold of it, his back leg shooting up with the effort
tucked out to mid-on now
outside off, swept round behind square
swivelled in from outside off, driven back out straight without too much trouble or power
on off, good length, driven back out to mid-on, the score just ticking over now
outside off, turned out a touch, the batsman rocks back to give himself room to cut out
outside off, driven off the back foot into the covers
down on one knee early, the ball dies on to leg and is swivel-swept round through fine leg
comes out on off to meet a regulation delivery, played forward on the front foot
very wide down leg, Ponting goes to sweep it, comes round too late on the shot and it goes past Dhoni unsurprisingly, then they run three
defended on the front foot this time
driven out to mid-on now
backs away on the back foot, drives out to mid-off and Ponting instructs: "Wait there, Pup!"
down leg and Clarke goes for the pull, connects hard but picks out Rohit Sharma who sticks out his hands to his right and takes a firm catch
full and wide down off, driven out to the covers first up
outside off, punched off the middle but without much power to the covers
bends back in from outside off, defended into the ground forward
outside off, pushed off the back foot to the covers
outside off, driven to the covers again on the front foot, just past the diving fielder
a quiet defence this time
rocks back and uses all available power to cut hard through the covers and nearly to the rope
worked out to short midwicket off the back foot from off
on leg and a touch short, turned round to midwicket
Ponting goes aerial now with a huge drive wide of mid-on and Ishant comes round to collect, just managing to keep the ball in the rope with a big dive
turned back in from outside off, defended on the front foot
more of the same, keeping him quiet for two balls
outside off, forced off the back foot to mid-on
outside off, worked out to mid-on
defended on the front foot
width outside off, cut to point
can't force it away again, too good in his line and length, defended on the back foot
worked out to mid-on now
reaches out down leg as the ball strays down there to sweep it to fine leg
cuts in a touch from outside off, short, and is pulled out to square
a full delivery on off, driven out to mid-off for a quick single
another seamless single
clips from outside off through square and they look for the two
comes back in off the seam outside off, pushed to the covers and they look for the quick single
short ball cramps up Ponting given its awkward bounce, tucked down off the back foot
driven back to mid-off
defended on the front foot this time
cut out to point
driven back forward towards the bowler
and again
driven right back to mid-on
comes out of his crease to meet the ball on line with off, driving hard through the covers
very tight on off, Symonds makes room to cut back through gully - not much room there at all, really
straight ball on off, the batsman comes out looking for the drive and has to adjust at the last second to defend on the front foot
on middle and leg, good length, driven out to mid-on
on a good line and length, the batsman comes out of his crease and defends on the front foot
on off, a quick single to mid-on to retain the strike
right up there on off, Ponting presses forward defensively without too much trouble
and again he is solid in defence
room outside off, and driven out through the covers
turned in on leg, driven back out to mid-on
comes out and defends on the front foot
worked back down off the back foot to gully
fullish delivery on middle and leg, pushed out off the back foot to short midwicket
down the track and a trademark shot as Symonds drives hard and aerial straight past the bowler
driven back forward this time
on leg, Ponting pulls round through square for another single
waits on leg, and fast hands whip the ball - having to make all of the power themselves - in front of square
up there on off, and defended on the front foot
driven on the front foot straight to cover
turned in to a good length in line with off, driven out to the covers
turns back in, he whips it back out to the gully and there's a half-appeal
waited and drove inside with a fullsome aerial drive over cover
defended solidly on the front foot
another booming drive through the covers
across the right hander just outside off, Ponting waits and then flicks down behind gully for another single to take him on the brink of his century
defended forward
outside off, short, and pulled round strongly in front of midwicket
swung on to leg, clipped out to square
a back foot defence to point
driven forward to mid-off for his century, his second ODI ton at the SCG and his 26th overall, that coming up off 111 balls
goes over the top now some of the pressure if off, with a cover drive
cut into the ground on off this time
outside off, driven out to the covers now
outside off, a touch short, Symonds looks to pull it through midwicket, the ball going back into the ground
outside off, Ponting follows it and cuts into the ground
comes out and does what Symonds just did - pulled hard into the ground, not quite timing it
driven out to mid-on
turned out to midwicket now
and to midwicket again
Symonds steps down and beasts the ball from outside off with a full-blooded shot wide of long-on
driven straight back through Harbhajan's fingers
a big wide down leg, seeing that Ponting was going to charge him
on the legs again, tighter this time though, and Ponting tucks it off his legs very fine
over the wicket across the right hander, Ponting drives out to long off, straight, and they hare back for the second
outside off, pulled to midwicket
outside off, Ponting gets down on one knee to meet a wideish one and drive aerially over extra cover
outside off again, driven out mid-off
greets a half-volley on off with a full drive through long-off and there was an easy two on
outside off, drives back into his pads, sets off, but scrambles back into his crease when he realises there isn't one on
low full toss, Symonds misses out by backing away and trying to force the cut through
outside off, low, sliced away down to third man off the back foot
slower ball, well disguised, Ponting was through the shot - a full-blooded drive outside off - before the ball was on to him
short ball, pulled out in front of Raina at deep midwicket, taking his eyes off the ball
driven out to the covers this time
full toss on leg, Symonds backs away and tris to force it out to the covers but a dot results
driven out to the leg-side for an easy run
slower ball outside off, short, and Symonds smashes the ball over midwicket for an entertaining fifty
jumps back into the leg-side, drives out off the back foot to the covers and they get back for a comfortable two
thigh-high full toss, Ponting drives hard to the covers
outside off, cut hard off the back foot through point. That was also a no-ball on height so no free hit, though an extra ball
outside off, driven out to mid-off
full ball on off and middle, driven out to long on
the slower ball pays dividends as Ishant cleans up Symonds with one which pitches on off and turns back in to take middle and off, Symonds moving back to leave the stumps exposed
a cheeky single to get Ponting back on sgtrike and Jussey would have been out if he had hit but Yuvraj's throw goes for overthrows to the short boundary
full toss quite high, Ponting peels off an aerial drive to mid-on
low one on middle and leg, whipped round behind square
slower ball again, dug out for a quick single
the change pays dividends as one comes in at 140kph, Ponting lashes out an aerial drive to long-off, and the leading edge is taken well by Irfan
outside off, pulled through midwicket
a good-length ball, pushed to the covers, Harbhajan scores a direct hit but Hopes was well in
slower ball, Hussey digs it from outside off to long-off, good running there from the pair
pushed up there in front of middle and leg, brushed out to square
a swing and a miss down off, the batsman trying to take it from outside off through midwicket and getting nowhere near it
wide outside off, Hussey shuffles across to meet it and drives wide of long-off
pushed out to mid-on from outside off
gets away with a cross-batted swat aimed towards square but which looped over the keeper from the top edge, a slower slower ball from Harbhajan
low full toss driven hard out to long-off
outside off, pulled back to Harbhajan who picks it up cleanly and easily runs out Hopes at the non-striker's
wide outside off, Hussey drives into the ground, Harbhajan picks up the ball and runs out Lee even despite a fumble

inn2.comm: short and cut fiercely, runs away to deep third man
opened the face to third man, cutely done

got 'em! big wicket for Lee, fires on into middle and leg, Tendulkar tries to swish across the line but can't make contact, huge appeal from Lee and the umpire, after thinking for a while, gives it out, he's on his way here and that was a big one for Lee
huge appeal for caught behind, that was down the leg side and Sehwag tries to flick, some sound there for sure, it was probably a deflection off the thigh pad, umpire Harper is unmoved
turned away towards square
tapped to the off side, that was slightly short of a length and he put it away in the gap
down the leg side, he tries to whack it across the line but can't make contact, wide called and rightly so
short of a length, on the body and pulled away in front of square, Sehwag in the mood here, it seems
full and on off, defended solidly on the front foot
good length ball, on middle stump, that's an accurate Bracken for you, Gambhir cramped for room and can only drop it close to his body, soft hands
sliding down leg again and Sehwag does the sensible thing, jumps up and uses Lee's pace to turn it down to the fine-leg fence, that was fast but Sehwag used the pace intelligently
short of a length, pushes firmly to the off side on the jump, three patrolling the cover region
fine short ball, getting extra zip off the track, 143kph that time, Sehwag is hurried onto it that time
that's creamed away, full and slightly wide and he's smoked that through the covers for four, burnt the grass on its way,
short of a length and cracks it straight to point, he's finding the meat of the bat here
and four more, he's on a roll here, down the leg side again, flicked away effortlessly for four more, the faster they come, the faster they go off the bat, Lee is quick but Sehwag is quicker
short and wide, cut and a miss, edgy from Gambhir
wide of the stumps again, taps it away from his body, straight to gully
cut to point, Clarke is prowling there and they don't take the single
short of a length and wide, another cut and a miss, he's having a bit of a nervy time here
breaks the shackles, full and on off, gets his front foot forward and smacks it on the move, once he finds the gap it races away, great value for shots here in Sydney, it's such a cracking pitch this
short of a length and close to his body, he cuts anyway and picks up a couple to third man
short of a length, slightly wide, Sehwag throws the kitchen sink at it but can't make contact, the extra bounce does him in
short again and Sehwag smacks it towards point, super effort from Michael Clarke, who stops a certain boundary, keeps them down to a single
patted to the off side, cautious that time
turned to square leg, they think of a single but the fielder takes a shy at the non-striker's end
short one but not as short as Gambhir anticipated, he tries to pull but can't gauge the bounce, is struck on the pads instead
short of a length and straight, Sehwag backs away and tries to smash it through the off side, slightly wide of point where they picked up a single
charging Bracken now, Gambhir is in a hurry, can't make contact to a full one that moves away a shade
full and on off, tapped to point, fine bowling from Bracken here, he's not giving anything away
cut away towards gully, Ponting, who is at the slips, cleans up

super Symonds gets into the act, Gambhir drives to the covers and takes off but Symonds dives and pulls of a fantastic one-handed save, throws towards the non-striker's end but can't get the diirect hit, Gambhir was not even in the picture then. Bracken was applauding the effort and not looking to get back instead
driven to cover
short of a length, defended off the back foot
flicked behind square, too much leg-side from Lee
majestic pull from Gambhir, he's pulled that out of nowhere, short and speedy ball from Lee and that's been crunched with immense power in front of square for a four, what a cracker!
turned away towards midwicket and they pick up three, fine running there, both play for Delhi and you expect them to have an understanding
punched off the back foot, good over from India, 9 off it

full and outside off, tries to drive but only manages a top edge over the slips, now they take on Lee's arm and this is big trouble, ball fired into Gilchrist but it's Sehwag who is in trouble in the non-striker's end, poor throw from Gilchrist and Bracken doesn't collect it, that was reckless
driven to cover
wafting outside off, beaten by the bounce and is lucky that didn't take the edge
pushed off the front foot, on the move to cover

down the track and, oh, that could have easily deflected back onto the stumps, races towards fine leg and Gilchrist runs after it because there's nobody else there, he dives full length towards the end, football style, but can't stop that one
cut and a miss outside off
short and wide of off stump, slower that time and doesn't bounce too much, Sehwag tries to pull but can't account for the lack of bounce
short of a length, turned away from middle to leg
outside off, tapped away towards third man

edged and taken! short of a length and he tries to turn it to third man, faint edge and Gilchrist takes a good low catch, big appeal and it's given immediately, India in trouble here, replays showed there was a thin edge
good length ball on off, 129kph, pushed to cover
pushed towards midwicket for a quick one

fantastic ball to get a big wicket, short of a length, angled across the right-hander, takes the edge and Gilchrist does the rest, he was fishing aimlessly there and Bracken sent down a beauty, good pace and subtle movement, India slip further
good length ball, tapped to the off side for a quick single and what an effort, Symonds picks up the ball and throws down the stumps in one motion
good length and outside off, shoulders arms, Gambhir has just seen two quick wickets fall, wonder what's going through his mind
short of a length, outside off again, left alone
driven crisply to cover, Hussey picks it up
too wide this time, Gambhir can't even reach it, but the umpire lets it go, no wide called, he was lucky there
cracking shot, forced off the back foot through the covers, really lashed into it as the ball came on to the bat and he took only three or four steps afterwards, stopping as he knew it was a four
but gone this time! Yuvraj walks as Clark pushes that one across him and he looks to crouch into a cut but fishes only through to the keeper
lets this one go wide down the channel
off the mark with a four, clipping one through square off his toes, the ball just outside the line of leg there
jumps into the line of off, defending down off the back foot as he goes
outside off and again he jumps into the line to defend down on the back foot
nips back in from outside off to middle and played forward, defensively
just outside off, back of a length, cut down to the gully
short outside off and he climbs into a huge cut through point, racing through the gap and on to the rope, shot and a half that one
swung into the right hander in line with off, and it's defended on the front foot
outside off, defended on the front foot now
pushed through down off, left alone
pushed up there in line with off, defended on the front foot
tight line, straight delivery, stump to stumps, pushed forward defensively, Ponting picks up and takes the non-striker's stumps just in case
played off the back foot into the covers
nipped back in from outside off, defended down
full ball, trademark yorker, well dug out
and another from his armoury, the straight bouncer, the batsman ducking under
appeal for lbw which isn't even entertained by the umpire who walks off quickly, not interested
lovely delivery from Clark, hitting the deck just outside off and carrying on away with the swing, nearly taking the outside edge
turned down off the back foot, defensively, the ball rising up
slower delivery at 124kph, rolling his fingers over, and defended down
dragged down just a touch, defended off the back foot into the covers
a touch of width outside off, waits and cuts back behind point
right up there, defended on the front foot, no run possible
shuttles through outside off, a good lick and a good length, the batsman is so not interested his first and only movement is a leave
down off, drags it a touch shorter and the batsman drives out off the back foot, jumping back as he plays the shot and that travels
pushed right up there, ticked off into the off-side, towards cover in fact and they race on
pushed down leg, the ball foisted off the thigh pad and they run a leg bye
down leg, typical Dhoni, he's on to it in a flash with a flick of the wrists through fine
full delivery on middle and leg, driven out to mid-on
a fairly short ball outside off, cut hard to deep point off the back foot
outside off, cut down behind point this time
outside off, turned into the covers off the back foot this time
